==Records==
[[File:ITFC Attendances.png|right|thumb|300px|alt=Graph of attendances at Portman Road since 1936|Average and highest attendances at the ground since [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] turned professional]]
The highest attendance recorded at Portman Road is 38,010 for a match against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] in the [[FA Cup]] sixth round on 8 March 1975.<ref name=fggatt>{{cite web|url=http://www.footballgroundguide.com/ipswich_town/#Record%20Attendance|title=Record & Average Attendance|last=Duncan Adams|date=21 February 2012 (updated)|work=Ipswich Town: Portman Road|publisher=Football Ground Guide|accessdate=22 March 2012}}</ref>  The record modern (all-seated) attendance is 30,152, set on 21 December 2003 against local rivals [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] in [[Football League Division One]].<ref name=fggatt/>  The largest crowd for a non-competitive game at the ground was over 23,000 for Bobby Robson's testimonial where Ipswich, including [[George Best]], played against an England XI.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.colorsport.co.uk/galleries/football/george-best-turns-out-for-ipswich|title=GEORGE BEST TURNS OUT FOR IPSWICH TOWN|publisher=Colorspot Images Ltd|accessdate=19 March 2012}}</ref>

The highest seasonal average at the stadium since Ipswich turned professional was 26,431 in the [[1976<U+2013>77 in English football|1976<U+2013>77]] season while Ipswich were playing in the [[Football League First Division|First Division]].  The lowest average attendance at Portman Road was 8,741 in the club's inaugural league season, the [[1936<U+2013>37 in English football|1936<U+2013>37]] season in [[Football League Third Division South|Division Three (South)]].

The highest total seasonal attendance was recorded during the [[1980<U+2013>81 in English football|1980<U+2013>81]] season when the aggregate was more than 814,000 during a season in which Ipswich won the [[1981_UEFA_Cup_Final#Final|UEFA Cup]] and finished second in the First Division.<ref>{{Cite web
| url = http://www.tmwmtt.com/sql/attendances.phtml
| title = Attendances since 1936 (all competitions)
| publisher = Pride of Anglia
| accessdate =18 January 2008
}} {{subscription required}}</ref>

Portman Road hosted Ipswich Town's first appearance in European football competition when they defeated [[Floriana F.C.|Floriana]] of Malta 10<U+2013>0, still a club record, in the [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]] in 1962.<ref>{{Cite web
| url = http://www.fchd.info/IPSWICHT.HTM
| title = Ipswich Town
| publisher = fchd.info
| accessdate =23 January 2008
| archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20100414041921/http://www.fchd.info/IPSWICHT.HTM
| archivedate = 14 April 2010
}}</ref>  Since then, Ipswich Town remain undefeated at Portman Road in all European competitions, a total of 31 matches spanning 40 years,<ref>{{cite news
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/uefa_cup/2376187.stm
| title = Ipswich edge out Liberec
| accessdate =23 January 2008
| date = 31 October 2002
|publisher=BBC Sport
}}</ref> a record until it was surpassed by [[AZ (football club)|AZ Alkmaar]] in December 2007.<ref>{{Cite news
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/7145803.stm
| title = AZ Alkmaar 2<U+2013>3 Everton
| author = Caroline Cheese
|publisher=BBC Sport
| accessdate =23 January 2008
| date = 20 December 2007
}}  AZ Alkmaar were defeated in the match after breaking the record total; this could allow the record to be regained by Ipswich Town should they qualify for Europe in the future and remain undefeated in their next two home games.</ref>

==Transport==
The stadium is approximately {{convert|450|yd|m}} from [[Ipswich railway station]], which lies on the [[Great Eastern Main Line]] from [[London Liverpool Street]] to [[Norwich]]. The stadium has no parking facilities for supporters, and the streets around the ground are subject to a residents-only permit parking scheme, but there are a number of [[pay and display]] or [[park and ride]] car parks within a short distance of the ground.<ref name=stands/><ref>{{Cite web
| url = http://www.multimap.com/maps/?hloc=GB%7Cipswich#t=l&map=52.05276,1.14571%7C17%7C4&loc=GB:52.05986:1.15548:14%7Cipswich%7CIpswich,%20Suffolk,%20England,%20IP1%203
| title = Ipswich
| publisher = [[Multimap]]
| accessdate =19 January 2008
}}</ref>

